comment: ExVM Assembler Specification. This defines the base syntax for the assembler.

LDQ.comment: Load a small (0-15) integer literal into the specified register

LD_I16_8.comment: Load an 16-bit integer literal into the specified register as a truncated 8-bit value

LD_I16_16.comment: Load a 16-bit integer literal into the specified register as a 16-bit value

LD_I16_32.comment: Load a 16-bit integer literal into the specified register as an extended 32-bit value

LD_I16_64.comment: Load a 16-bit integer literal into the specified register as an extended 64-bit value

LD_I32_32.comment: Load a 32-bit integer literal into the specified register as a 32-bit value

LD_I32_64.comment: Load a 32-bit integer literal into the specified register as an extended 64-bit value

LD_F32.comment: Load a 32-bit float literal into the specified register as a 32-bit value

LD_RI_8.comment: Load an 8-bit integer value referenced by the source register into the destination register

LD_RI_16.comment: Load a 16-bit integer value referenced by the source register into the destination register

LD_RI_32.comment: Load a 32-bit integer or float value referenced by the source register into the destination register

LD_RI_64.comment: Load a 64-bit integer or float value referenced by the source register into the destination register

LD_RIPI_8.comment: Load an 8-bit integer value referenced by the source register into the destination register, then increment the source register

LD_RIPI_16.comment: Load a 16-bit integer value referenced by the source register into the destination register, then increment the source register

LD_RIPI_32.comment: Load a 32-bit integer or float value referenced by the source register into the destination register, then increment the source register

LD_RIPI_64.comment: Load a 64-bit integer or float value referenced by the source register into the destination register, then increment the source register

LD_RIPD_8.comment: Decrement the source register, then load an 8-bit integer value referenced by the source register into the destination register

LD_RIPD_16.comment: Decrement the source register, then load a 16-bit integer value referenced by the source register into the destination register

LD_RIPD_32.comment: Decrement the source register, then load a 32-bit integer or float value referenced by the source register into the destination register

LD_RIPD_64.comment: Decrement the source register, then load a 64-bit integer or float value referenced by the source register into the destination register
